@Remark ------------------------------------------------------------------
@node whatitis
A device for informing you of the exact quantum of your existance.... Yeah,
yeah, it's a clock.

@endnode
@Remark ------------------------------------------------------------------
@node why "Why?"
Firstly, because I was bored and when I'm bored I either play Elvira
Mistress Of The Dark or I program, and as Elvira doesn't work on my
4000/40, my choice was limited.

Secondly, because I missed Babylon 5.

Thirdly, because it's there.


@endnode
@Remark ------------------------------------------------------------------
@node howdoidoit "How do I do it?"
It is dead easy. All you do is follow these steps...

1) Double click on the icon, or I suppose you could put it in WBStartup.

That's it.


@endnode
@Remark ------------------------------------------------------------------
@node limitations "Limitations..."
There is no alarm facility, but I might add one if you want.
@endnode
@Remark ------------------------------------------------------------------
@node systemrequirements "System Requirements..."
It was written on a 3.0 A4000/40 with 2 meg chip, 8 meg fast and a
GVP ioExtender. It should run on any 2.0 machine, below that I don't know
and I'm not dismembering my Lorraine to find out!

@endnode
